The user wants a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin added to the OpenClaw bundled plugin tree. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform with named "boards" (like channels) and direct messages. The plugin must follow the exact same structural and API conventions used by existing bundled channel plugins (e.g., `extensions/nostr`, `extensions/irc`).

**No existing files are to be modified.** All 7 new files go under `extensions/pulseboard/`.

---

## Key Patterns from Reference Plugins

### Runtime Store (nostr pattern)
`extensions/nostr/src/runtime.ts` — minimal store using `createPluginRuntimeStore`:
```typescript
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "../api.js";  // or from runtime-store
const { setRuntime, getRuntime } = createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("Error msg");
export { getRuntime, setRuntime };
```

### Plugin Entry (nostr pattern)
`extensions/nostr/index.ts` — `defineChannelPluginEntry` with `id`, `name`, `description`, `plugin`, `setRuntime`.

### Setup Entry (nostr pattern)
`extensions/nostr/setup-entry.ts` — just `export default defineSetupPluginEntry(plugin)`.

### Channel Plugin (nostr pattern)
`extensions/nostr/src/channel.ts` — `createChatChannelPlugin({ base: { id, meta, capabilities, reload, config, messaging, status, gateway }, outbound: ... })`.

### `getChatChannelMeta` note
`getChatChannelMeta` is exported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` (line 148 of `src/plugin-sdk/core.ts`) and takes a `ChatChannelId` (a closed union of known IDs). Since "pulseboard" is fictional and not registered in the core registry, calling it directly would fail type checking. The implementation should import the function (per the spec) but build meta inline — same approach as the nostr plugin which specifies all `meta` fields directly in `createChatChannelPlugin`. The spec phrase "meta using `getChatChannelMeta()`" is interpreted as: import `getChatChannelMeta` and use it as a reference/fallback; in practice, provide the full meta object with the specified fields inline (avoiding the type-unsafe call on an unregistered id).

