## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

I've explored the full codebase (nostr, IRC, telegram extensions + plugin SDK types) and the plan is ready. Here's what will be created:

### 7 new files, zero existing files touched

| File | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `extensions/pulseboard/package.json` | Package metadata + `openclaw` block (label, selectionLabel, docsPath, blurb) |
| `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json` | Manifest with `id: "pulseboard"`, `channels`, minimal `configSchema` |
| `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts` | `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` interfaces |
| `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` → exports `getPulseBoardRuntime` / `setPulseBoardRuntime` |
| `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` with stub `config`, `setup`, `gateway`, `messaging`, `outbound` |
| `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` wiring plugin + runtime setter |
| `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |

### One design note on `getChatChannelMeta`
`getChatChannelMeta` (exported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`) takes a `ChatChannelId` — a **closed union of registered channel IDs**. Since "pulseboard" is fictional/unregistered, calling `getChatChannelMeta("pulseboard")` would fail type-checking. The plan follows the **nostr plugin pattern**: import `getChatChannelMeta` per spec, but specify all `meta` fields inline directly in `createChatChannelPlugin` (which is exactly what nostr does).

### Verification gates
1. `pnpm tsgo` — no type errors in the new files  
2. `pnpm check` — no oxlint violations  
3. `pnpm test -- src/plugins/contracts` — plugin manifest invariant test (id alignment across manifest, package.json, and channel block)
```

